 The Governing Council of Lagos State University (LASU), Ojo, has shortlisted nine professors for the vacant vice chancellor seat. Prof. Oyedamola Oke is the acting Vice Chancellor of the institution. Following the close of submission of application, it was learnt that 13 professors from within and outside LASU applied for the position. The Governing Council had adopted an unconventional interview method. Thus, the nine professors will write a Computer-Based Test (CBT). A breakdown shows that seven internal professors were shortlisted for the interview scheduled to hold on March 11 at the Lagos State University College of Medicine (LASUCOM), Ikeja. The remaining two shortlisted professors are from other institutions. One is a don in Namibia. It was learnt that from the seven internal candidates, two do not have PhD. The internal candidates are Prof. Akinyemi Kabir, Faculty of Science; Prof. Elias Wahab, current Deputy Vice Chancellor; Prof. Sena Bakre, Faculty of Science. Others include, Prof.  Ibiyemi-Bello Olatunji, LASUCOM; Prof. Olumuyiwa Odusanya, LASUCOM; Prof. Dideolu Awofoju, Namibia; Prof. Abiodun Adewuya, acting Provost of LASUCOM and Prof. Ayodeji Badejo, former Dean, Faculty of Education.